%% Figure 3.6 — State diagram: Paper preview/save/export lifecycle.
%% QForge — Paper lifecycle state diagram (Chapter 3, §3.1.3).
%% Reconciled against the Post-M6 preview/save lifecycle (docs/MILESTONES.md Post-M6 row):
%% `generate` persists NOTHING — it returns an unsaved preview (id = null) plus a seed;
%% an explicit Save (POST /papers) re-generates deterministically from that seed and
%% persists as status = saved; export sets status = exported. The `draft` enum value is
%% legacy (M2/M3) and no longer produced by the current flow.
stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> Preview : POST /papers/generate (unsaved, id = null, + seed)
    Preview --> Preview : regenerate (new seed)
    Preview --> Saved : POST /papers (persist, re-run from seed)
    Saved --> Exported : GET /papers/{id}/export (pdf | docx)
    Exported --> Exported : re-export (export_count++)
    Saved --> [*] : delete
    Exported --> [*] : delete

    note right of Preview
        Discarded if never saved —
        no history clutter.
    end note
